getAddress

public javax.telephony.Address getAddress(java.lang.String number)
                                   throws javax.telephony.InvalidArgumentException
Get the Address object associated with a certain number.

If this is not already known, we may query the Raw telephony provider and create the dynamic Address on the fly. This occurs if the raw telephony provider did not return a static Address set or if the (non-strict-JTAPI) case where dynamic Addresses are allowed on top of the static Address set.

Specified by:
getAddress in interface javax.telephony.Provider
Tags copied from interface: javax.telephony.Provider
Parameters:
number - The telephone address string.
Returns:
The Address object corresponding to the given telephone number.
Throws:
javax.telephony.InvalidArgumentException - The name, e.g. telephone number of the Address does not correspond to the name of any Address object known to the Provider or within the Provider's domain.
